      <h2>The Manufacturing Challenge: Growing Without Draining Cash</h2>

      <p>Running a factory in Malaysia is rewarding but capital-intensive. Whether you are in food production, plastic molding, or metal fabrication, the machines you use are the heart of your business. But here is the problem: new production lines cost hundreds of thousands, if not millions, of Ringgit. If you pay cash, your bank balance hits zero. If you go to a bank, they ask for a 20% down payment and a mountain of paperwork.</p>

      <p>At Ing Heng Credit, we understand Malaysian manufacturing. We know that sometimes you need that CNC machine or packing line <em>right now</em> to fulfill a big order. That is why we offer manufacturing equipment financing that works with your cash flow, not against it.</p>

      <h2>Types of Machinery We Finance</h2>

      <p>We do not just look at the brand; we look at the utility. If the machine helps your factory produce and earn, we can likely finance it. This includes:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>CNC Machines:</strong> Lathes, mills, and routers for precision engineering.</li>
        <li><strong>Injection Molding:</strong> For plastic product manufacturers.</li>
        <li><strong>Food Processing Equipment:</strong> Industrial ovens, mixers, and automated packing lines.</li>
        <li><strong>Woodworking Machinery:</strong> Saws, edgebanders, and sanding machines.</li>
        <li><strong>Metalworking Tools:</strong> Hydraulic presses, shearing machines, and laser cutters.</li>
        <li><strong>Packaging Systems:</strong> Labeling machines, vacuum sealers, and conveyors.</li>
      </ul>

