      <h2>Real World Example: SME Success Story</h2>

      <p>Meet Mr. Tan. He runs a small plastic injection molding factory in Klang. He had the chance to sign a major contract with an electronics firm, but he needed two more machines to meet the production volume. The machines (used) were RM180,000 each.</p>

      <p>His bank rejected him because the machines were 12 years old. He did not have RM360,000 in cash to buy them outright. He came to us. We looked at his business, saw the contract he had signed, and approved a 100% loan for both machines. He started production the following week. Today, his monthly revenue has tripled, and he is easily paying off the installments while keeping his cash flow healthy.</p>

      <h2>How Industry 4.0 Changes Financing</h2>

      <p>You might have heard about "Industry 4.0" and smart manufacturing. It sounds complicated, but it just means using better technology to be more efficient. Investing in sensors, automated arms, or better software can qualify you for certain tax benefits in Malaysia, such as the Capital Allowance.</p>

      <p>When you finance your equipment with Ing Heng Credit, you still get to enjoy these tax benefits. You own the machine (through hire purchase), so you can claim the depreciation against your company tax. It is a double win: you keep your cash, and you pay less tax.</p>

